text.text:
This place is pretty small. The table we sat at was a high top and pretty uncomfortable. There wasn’t enough room on the table for our food.

The bartender was so nice though. After she saw I didn’t drink my drink she asked if I wanted to swap and I did! It didn’t like it at all. I got the color and co. Which looked gorgeous. But didn’t taste sweet and fruity like the description said. Maybe it was the egg whites I didn’t like but I thought the drink tasted like plastic. She made me a paper plane with no complaints and that was good.

The happy hour deals are pretty good, for $20 you can get two share plates or an entree and a share plate. The food was just okay though. The chicken sandwhich was pretty spicy and was covered in coleslaw or something. I liked the big pickle with it though. The chicken wings were too spicy too and kind of dry. The salad I had should have been bigger.

If you are in the area I recommend to try another place for food.

text.text: First time here tonight, I love the vibe and seating here. My friends and I took a booth near the entrance and the music/ambiance volume is at a good level where you can carry regular volume conversation which was what we were looking for, something chill. The neon light is really cute in front. Had the chicken burrito which was yummy. The hurricane cocktail was a favorite. Young was our bartender and really appreciate their awesome service and great tasting drinks!

text.text: Finally got to try out Bosco after a few friends' high recommendations. Went during brunch and the ambiance and decor were so nice! Sat at the bar and after the bartender being so attentive and checking in on our food and drinks, I would say this was the best brunch experience I've had in Greenwich Village. Their loaded nachos were so yummy and I would highly recommend any of their spritzes for summertime!

overview.text: Tacos and other Mexican eats share the menu with Latin-inspired cocktails at this craft bar.

description.text:
Cozy Greenwich Village cocktail bar offering Mexican food and brunch.
The menu features dishes such as tacos, guacamole, chicken wings, and elote. Customers like the drinks, including margaritas and mezcal negronis.
There's a happy hour, as well as live music and trivia nights. People appreciate the fast service and the friendly, attentive staff.
Customers typically spend $20–30.

editorialSummary.text: Gluten-free versions of classic Italian dishes offered in a warm, intimate atmosphere.

text.text: Enjoyed every single thing I ate at this establishment. I'm not from NY so I made sure to make time to come here during my trip. It did not disappoint! It felt so great to eat delicious food without being worried about safety (I'm a newly diagnosed celiac). I will come here every time I'm in NYC, so you should go too!

text.text: For those Gluten free this is a must try. You can get your Italian fix with the great staff and helpful service. The lasagna and Mushroom Ravioli were delightful. Chicken parm you can skip.

text.text:
"I recently dined with my family and was thoroughly impressed. The menu offers a fantastic variety of gluten-free dishes, all of which were delicious and beautifully presented. From the appetizers to the desserts, every bite was a culinary delight.

The service was equally outstanding. The staff was knowledgeable, attentive, and went above and beyond to ensure a wonderful dining experience. I highly recommend for anyone seeking amazing gluten-free cuisine and exceptional service."

text.text: If you’re celiac/GF- you’ve got to go here! It’s incredible to not have to worry about any cross contamination. The ambiance is very much like a little slice of Italy in New York. overview.text: Gluten-free Italian cuisine is served at this casual restaurant with a full bar.

description.text:
Cozy, romantic restaurant in Greenwich Village offering 100% gluten-free Italian food for lunch and dinner, plus dessert, coffee, and cocktails. Vegetarian and healthy options are available.
Popular dishes include pasta, lasagna, and tiramisu.
Diners say the staff is attentive and the service is fast. The owner is described as sweet. Some people praise the atmosphere.
Customers typically spend $30–50.

text.text: Leny was the best waiter! Kitchen was closing and he was able to find us a table super quickly and we were able to eat.

text.text: Absolutely in love with this place! Been here multiple times because of my gluten and dairy allergies. Owner is super sweet and staff is super attentive. Definitely go here, I bring my non allergy friends too!

text.text: Overall I’d give Senza Gluten a 3.5 rating. I’m incredibly thankful that there is a space to have a 100% gluten free meal that’s safe for celiacs. The restaurant is typically busy and the staff is overwhelmed but remain professional and kind. There are a lot of options and the food is pretty good.  I find the food to be incredibly expensive for the quality. While you get a decent portion size for appetizers and mains the desserts are tiny and all cost $17 or more. I ordered the cannoli and received 2 pinky sized cannolis at almost $10 each, it’s a bit insulting. I’ll always go back because of the need to eat gluten free but I’ll just go around the corner to poshpop bakery if I feel like dessert.

text.text: What a gem! I stumbled on this place in the heart of the village amongst a sea of restaurants. They have an amazing brunch and great drink specials. I had the best Huevos Rancheros i ever had. The manager was very sweet and very inviting which is so refreshing these days. The bartender was very nice and professional and they  had this great jazz band playing as well. Kudos to the chef and team at Ways and Means. I definitely will be back for sure!

text.text: Went here to celebrate a birthday. 1st time visiting a live comedy show. Unfortunately, there was only myself, my bf and one other person for the show so they informed us that they were going to cancel. They offered us a partial refund or the opportunity to come back to another show. We explained that it was a special night and that we were really looking forward to this event. They then offered to do the show for us three and it was such an awesome experience. The comedians were great, we were so appreciative of them continuing the show and will definitely be back for more!

text.text: I don’t say this lightly - this might be the best all around menu in Manhattan. The burger is one of my favorites I’ve had in the city, and the cocktails are AMAZING! The bartenders are very fun and easy to talk to and all of the staff is welcoming and friendly. Amazing brunch, professional grade espresso machine for lattes, amazing drinks, AND they have comedy shows in the back every day. Perfect place to become a regular at.

text.text: Very quaint little spot in the Village. The food was delicious. No lie. Seriously the food is crazy good. I ordered the steak quesadilla and my wife ordered the Chicken Alfredo and a side of fries and some fried calamari. The steak quesadilla was full with great seasoned chunks of steak. It came with a side of guacamole,sour cream and salsa. OMG. I recommend 👌🏼. Had a taste of the chicken Alfredo. And it was out of this world. Fries were good. It's fries. The fried calamari was ok. But good. Can't knock them for that. Service was awesome. Very friendly. Coming back to try some more on the menu.
